nited Kingdom","Braybrooke, Northamptonshire, England":"Braybrooke, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Braybrooke","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Braybrook  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Braybrook","meanings":["English: locative name from Braybrooke (Northants)."]}]},{"name":"Gerald","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’ + <i>wald</i> ‘rule’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. There has been some confusion with   Gerard .  It died out in England at the end of the 13th century. However, it continued to be popular in Ireland, where it had been brought in the 12th century at the time of Strongbow's invasion. It was used in England in the 17th century and revived in the 19th century, along with several other long-extinct names of Norman, Old English, and Celtic origin, and is now more common than <i>Gerard</i>, which survived all along as an English ‘gentry’ name."],"variants":[{"name":"Jerrold","meanings":["Rare variant of   Gerald  , probably a transferred use of the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":26,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":51,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Gerald Braybrooke Sr was born in 1264, in Colmworth, Bedfordshire, England, his father, John de Braybrooke, was 44 and his mother, Joan Weldebof, was 38. He married Lora Picott about 1289, in Warwickshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died before 1324, in Colmworth, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1264–Bef 1324":"1264–enne 1324","1264–1324":"1264–1324","1273–Female":"1273–Surnud","1307–1359":"1307–1359","1220–1293":"1220–1293","1227–1302":"1227–1302","AFT 1302":"pärast 1302","1264":"1264","1220":"1220","Bef 1324":"enne 1324","1273":"1273","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1227":"1227","1359":"1359","1302":"1302","1324":"1324","7 October 1307":"7. oktoober 1307","about 1289":"umbes 1289","1307":"1307","1317":"1317","Wake, Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, England","Colmworth, Bedford, England":"Colmworth, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Colmworth, Bedfordshire, England":"Colmworth, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Braybrooke, Northamptonshire, England":"Braybrooke, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1264–Bef 1324":"1264–ennen vuotta 1324","1264–1324":"1264–1324","1273–Female":"1273–Kuollut","1307–1359":"1307–1359","1220–1293":"1220–1293","1227–1302":"1227–1302","AFT 1302":"1302 jälkeen","1264":"1264","1220":"1220","Bef 1324":"ennen vuotta 1324","1273":"1273","1293":"1293","1290":"1290","1315":"1315","1227":"1227","1359":"1359","1302":"1302","1324":"1324","7 October 1307":"7. lokakuuta 1307","about 1289":"noin 1289","1307":"1307","1317":"1317","Wake, Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, England","Colmworth, Bedford, England":"Colmworth, Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Colmworth, Bedfordshire, England":"Colmworth, Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Braybrooke, Northamptonshire, England":"Braybrooke, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1264–Bef 1324":"1264–avant 1324","1